                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16676684" author="deki" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2018 12:18:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=reta&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;reta&quot;&gt;reta&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll suggest to change &lt;tt&gt;@ConditionalOnBean(OpenApiFeature.class)&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;@ConditionalOnClass(OpenApiFeature.class)&lt;/tt&gt;. Any objections?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16676858" author="reta" created="Tue, 6 Nov 2018 14:57:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=deki&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;deki&quot;&gt;deki&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot for finding that. Yes, I think&#160;@ConditionalOnClass(OpenApiFeature.class) it the safe change, the post-processor would be able to properly assign the customizer instance to the beans. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Best Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; Andriy Redko&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
